                    "isHidden": false
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Let me check your Maven dependencies in the pom.xml:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "toolCall",
                    "toolCallId": "toolu_01Y2ubmsEuD5dzbwarcx6GXg",
                    "statusText": "Viewed file",
                    "status": "SUCCESS",
                    "context": {
                        "files": [
                            {
                                "path": "pom.xml",
                                "fsPath": "C:\\Users\\DELL\\Desktop\\Assessment_Management_Sysytem\\Backend\\pom.xml"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "isHidden": false
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Now I understand the issue! Let me explain the H2 database configuration and fix the problem:\n\n## Explanation of H2 Database Configuration\n\n```properties\n# Database Configuration (H2 for development)\nspring.h2.console.enabled=true              # Enables H2 web console at /h2-console\nspring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb    # In-memory database named 'testdb'\nspring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver  # H2 database driver class\nspring.datasource.username=sa               # Default H2 username\nspring.datasource.password=password         # Database password\nspring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect  # Hibernate dialect for H2\n```\n\n## The Problem\n\nThe error \"Cannot resolve class 'Driver'\" occurs because **you don't have the H2 database dependency** in your `pom.xml`. Your current configuration is trying to use H2, but you only have MongoDB dependencies.\n\n## Solution\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1: Add H2 Dependencies (Recommended for development)\nAdd these dependencies to your `pom.xml`:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "toolCall",
                    "toolCallId": "toolu_019ez2qvPEQNZGxcSPCeUqyz",
                    "statusText": "Change generated",
                    "status": "SUCCESS",
                    "context": {
                        "files": [
                            {
                                "path": "pom.xml",
                                "fsPath": "C:\\Users\\DELL\\Desktop\\Assessment_Management_Sysytem\\Backend\\pom.xml"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "isHidden": false
                },
                {
                    "type": "codeHunk",
                    "lineBasedDiff": "--- pom.xml\n+++ pom.xml\n@@ -29,6 +29,21 @@\n         <dependency>\n             <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n             <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-mongodb</artifactId>\n+            <version>3.5.0</version>\n+        </dependency>\n+\n+        <!-- H2 Database for development -->\n+        <dependency>\n+            <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n+            <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n+            <version>2.2.224</version>\n+            <scope>runtime</scope>\n+        </dependency>\n+\n+        <!-- Spring Boot JPA Starter -->\n+        <dependency>\n+            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n+            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>\n             <version>3.5.0</version>\n         </dependency>\n ",
                    "refToolCallId": "toolu_019ez2qvPEQNZGxcSPCeUqyz"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "### Option 2: Use MongoDB Configuration Instead\n\nIf you prefer to use MongoDB (since you already have it), update your `application.properties`:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "toolCall",
                    "toolCallId": "toolu_01GSHFtBTnaTNFHLEo3M73pp",
                    "statusText": "Change generated",
                    "status": "SUCCESS",
                    "context": {
