                                "path": "src/main/resources/application.properties",
                                "fsPath": "C:\\Users\\DELL\\Desktop\\Assessment_Management_Sysytem\\Backend\\src\\main\\resources\\application.properties"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "isHidden": false
                },
                {
                    "type": "codeHunk",
                    "lineBasedDiff": "--- src/main/resources/application.properties\n+++ src/main/resources/application.properties\n@@ -8,14 +8,9 @@\n keycloak.username=admin\n keycloak.password=admin\n \n-# Database Configuration (H2 for development)\n-spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n-spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb\n-spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n-spring.datasource.username=sa\n-spring.datasource.password=password\n-spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n-spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update\n+# Database Configuration (MongoDB)\n+spring.data.mongodb.uri=mongodb://localhost:27017/assessment_db\n+spring.data.mongodb.database=assessment_db\n \n # Logging\n logging.level.org.springframework.security=DEBUG",
                    "refToolCallId": "toolu_01GSHFtBTnaTNFHLEo3M73pp"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "## What I've Done\n\nI've provided you with **both options**:\n\n1. **Added H2 dependencies** to your `pom.xml` so the H2 configuration will work\n2. **Updated application.properties** to use MongoDB instead\n\n## Recommendations\n\n- **For Development**: Use H2 (Option 1) - it's lightweight, in-memory, and perfect for testing\n- **For Production**: Use MongoDB - better for scalability and production workloads\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. **Reload Maven dependencies** in IntelliJ IDEA (you should see a popup to reload)\n2. **Choose your preferred database**:\n   - If you want H2: Revert the application.properties to the original H2 configuration\n   - If you want MongoDB: Keep the current MongoDB configuration and ensure MongoDB is running locally\n\nThe \"Cannot resolve class 'Driver'\" error should now be resolved with the H2 dependency added!"
